Package com.b2international.snowowl.datastore.server.cdo

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ICDOConflictProcessor
    Handles conflicting changes when synchronizing branches.
    IMergeConflictRule
    Generic interface for merge conflict rules
    IMergeConflictRuleProvider  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractCDOBranchAction
    Encapsulates a CDO branch-manipulating action which has the following properties: ensure that all branches and their parents are existing; a branch lock is acquired for all affected branches; the wrapped action is executed; thrown exceptions are caught and returned; locks are released when the action terminates for any reason.
    AbstractCDOConflictProcessor
    Abstract superclass for ICDOConflictProcessors that only want to report a subset of possible application-level conflicts.
    AddedInSourceAndDetachedInTargetConflict
    Reported when a component is added on the source branch, but it references a component (either directly or indirectly) which was detached on the target branch.
    AddedInSourceAndTargetConflict
    Reported when components with the same domain key are added on both the source and the target branch.
    AddedInTargetAndDetachedInSourceConflict
    Reported when a component is added on the target branch, but it references a component (either directly or indirectly) which was detached on the source branch.
    CDOBranchActionManager
    Application service class responsible for handling branch operations, eg.
    ConflictMapper  
    GenericConflict  
    IMergeConflictRuleProvider.NullImpl
    NOOP implementation of IMergeConflictRuleProvider
    NullCDOConflictProcessor
    The no-op implementation of ICDOConflictProcessor.
    PrepareBranchAction
    Creates task branches and freezes state in the parent branch index, so a differencing task index can be based on it.
    PromoteBranchAction
    Promotes changes from any task branch to its parent.
    SynchronizeBranchAction
    Synchronizes changes with the task branches' parents.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CDOConflictProcessorBroker
    Broker for terminology specific conflict processors.
